  "text": "Assessing the relationship between deprivation and health can be difficult. For instance, there is a well-established relationship between unemployment and negative health outcomes. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] As employment and income are the most heavily weighted components of the SIMD score, their effect is likely to be a driving contributor to the correlation between deprivation and antibiotic Interactions between age and sex (P, 0.001), age and deprivation (P, 0.001) and sex and deprivation (P¼0.006) were also included in the model. Overall model fit tested by the omnibus test (P,0.001).",
